Two men were shot early Saturday in Brooklyn, police said. The men were standing in the lobby of a building at 1144 Bergen St. in Crown Heights, when an unknown assailant shot one man in the head and the other in the torso, the NYPD said. The incident happened just before 1 a.m. The police did not publicly identify the victims. Both men were taken to Kings County Hospital when one man was in critical condition and the other was stable, police said. No arrests have been made yet in connection with the shooting.